file: .ctxignore
behavior: Defines the gitignore-syntax scope file that determines which source files the ctx summarization tools include or exclude when generating context documents.
edit_notes:
  - Seeded once from .gitignore by ctx-scan at initialization; .gitignore is never read again afterward, so this file is the sole source of truth for scope.
  - target/ exclusion plus secrets/binary denial are enforced on top of this file by the tooling and cannot be overridden here.
  - .context/ holds per-task cache/reports and is excluded, but rollup.ctx, *.ctx, and intent.md are committed and expected to exist despite the directory pattern.
functions:
invariants:
  - .env is always excluded; only .env.example (keyless template) is meant to be tracked.
external_deps: